caption: Food is delicious, and the Thai market downstairs is great!

I have ate at the restaurant at least a dozen times if not more, gotten take out for when I’ve had guests at home, and every time the quality of the food is amazing. And of course the service is always great 👍 Claudia the manager always takes good care of me 🙏

All of the food was excellent and quickly served- we ordered pad thai (uniquely served with a thin layer of scrambled egg on top), panang curry, larb gai (so spicy but good), and thai iced tea. They were also taking COVID precautions seriously and had an additional outdoor seating area sectioned off in a few parking spaces, where the tables were spaced out, staff wore masks, and served one time use utensils and cups. We'll definitely be back!
Favorite Thai in DC. Amazing pad see ew, drunken noodles, and curries.  Definitely recommend.
Amazing pad Thai and pad see ew! One of my favorite Thai places in DC!
Ordered take out. The chicken fried rice was absolutely bland and tasteless.  The chicken was dry and chewy.  The green curry was also very mediocre.  What a disappointment.
The food was delicious and.the service was excellent.   Definitely someplace you need to visit.
The best Thai food in Dc. We order it almost every week.
Excellent Thai food! Great flavor, friendly staff, fast service. I'll definitely be back!
Some dishes lacking the pizazz of yesteryear.
I loved the crispy red snapper salad dish. Came with sticky rice.

The food was good enough, but because of the service I give it a two star rating.  Firstly having a server ask you how long have you been in American for ,just because they feel entitled on demanding how much tip they should get is not any type of experience anyone should get. We got there and did not get any service that was even close enough to say it was a good restaurant experience overall!..the food made the experience good, but not the service.
Relic of the past
Delicious food!  Excellent GF menu!!
Hands down one of my top 3 favorite restaurants in DC. The staff and owner are always super nice, the food is always great, and the atmosphere is just fun.
Extremely attentive and wonderful staff. I will definitely be back in the future.
Food was ok, but I had the duck and it was a bit chewy
Greeted by the what looked like the owner or manager as if I was an inconvenience. Food was very average considering how well reviewed this place is.

This restaurant is one of the best kept secrets of 14th Street, most likely due to its humble exterior appearance. As soon as you enter, you're greeted by a cozy, modern atmosphere. The food is seriously incredible. It's my favorite Thai place in DC, and I go here a couple times a month. Flavors and quality are incredible, and pricing is about on par with the area. If you love Thai food, definitely give this place a try!
Great service and fantastic flavors! The pad thai was extremely light and bursting with flavors.

Delicious Thai food in a cosy atmosphere. The dinner menu has many vegetarian options (including curries, spring rolls, soups, noodles, etc). Friendly and attentive staff; served us quickly and suggested their best options. Fresh vegetarian spring rolls were huge and delicious!
Food was pretty good

A terrific place for good Thai food. The rice is amazing and very cleverly flavored. A good mix of traditional and new age dishes. I highly recommend the crispy red snapper. Minus one star because the takeout area detracts from the overall ambiance and can be distracting.

This is my second visit to RICE, my last visit was years ago. It’s changed a lot since the first time. It’s mostly Thai dishes. The pad Thai is very good, with a thin layer of scrambled egg over the whole dish. I also liked the pumpkin empanada (!) a lot - that’s not Thai, but the empanada is very light and about as well prepared as an empanada can be, I think. There aren’t as many vegetarian dishes as I’d like, but this is a good go-to place for those regular Thai dishes that I can eat over and over again. The service was very good, and the outdoor seating area is nice on a good late summer night.
Very tasty Thai food. A lot of flavor. Good portions and prices. Nice ambiance. I wish this place a lot of customers.
Best Thai place
Small quaint restaurant with flavorful Thai food.  Great customer service. Awesome ambiance.
Terrific food and service!
(Translated by Google) Good But the price is not worth the food  (Original) Buono Ma il prezzo non vale il cibo
What makes RICE so good and unique is of course their green sticky rice that comes with many of their entrees. Go to is the panang curry. One of my favorites in all of DC.

Rice is a great restaurant for quality food. I usually call in my order for lunch a couple times a month and it is always great. The do offer lunch discounted prices. I recommend the Beef Kapow (slightly spicy and very tender beef.) The owner is a great guy and now knows me by name. They also offer outdoor space and a happy hour.  I'd highly recommend.
Good service but both me and my friend's dishes only had about 4 pieces of shrimp each (the only protein in the whole dish).
The worst place in Washington DC, worst customer servers. Very rude people. Do NOT go to this place, safe your night.
Goid food but waiter mixed up orders
Great food,  good choices and service is attentive.
Honestly the best pad thai I have ever had. The restaurant itself was very nice and the prices were great. They also had a gluten free menu, which is impossible to find at most asian restaurants.
One of my favorite places to get Thai food. Please try. Lovely patio and interior space. Cozy sheek

This is one of the best asian fusion restaurants in 14th street. Great flavor, great dishes, nice asian beers, kind staff and good outside sitting. The times I've been there it's always easy to get a table since it's surrounded by "more hip" places or "better" restaurants... this place is much better, it might even be my No.1 in 14th street

I had a very good Green Thai curry tofu Bento box for lunch here, so if you're looking for vegan options they've got you covered. My girlfriend had a vegan Pad Thai (there was no issue preparing the dish without eggs). Their fresh spring rolls were excellent and the accompanying hoi sin sauce outstanding. The staff are friendly and accommodating and they cultivate a pleasant atmosphere which allows for uninterrupted conversation - ideal for a business lunch. The molded seats are comfortable too which would make longer dining experiences much more enjoyable.  When I visited, the restroom area was undergoing renovations which was the only aesthetically displeasing feature I noticed.
The yum beef appetizer was absolutely incredible.  The restaurant was open and comfortable; I'd definitely come back to eat
Service and food is consistently good.

One of my favorite Thai restaurants in the area. The larb appatizer is the best. Just enough spice! The curry combo let's you try their 3 amazing curries and is plenty for two. Welcoming staff, excellent food, great location!
Great Thai !!! The restaurant itself is spacious and tranquil. Loved the feel in there very cozy. The drunken noodles (photo below) are SOOO good. IF you don't mind a little spicy.

Excellent and efficient service for the entire time that we were sat at the table. We had a group of 9 come in and they made room for us very quickly. All members of our party received their orders promptly and were satisfied. The atmosphere of the establishment was also very nice and cozy. I will definitely be returning for future meals here!
Excellent curry!  Service is very good too.  Take an Uber though as parking is tough here.

This Thai restaurant was better than other ones  I've visited. The vegetables were done to perfection, I've actually never had broccoli that tasted this yummy. My first Margarita was good, my second just tasted like water. The staff could have done a better job at stopping by my table and asking if my guest and I needed anything (we waited over 20 min for a refill, and the restaurant is tiny), but I really did enjoy the ambiance of the space. Because of its location in Logan Circle, you will be spending some money here, but it's a nice treat. I recommend going during happy hour.
Best Thai around. Good portions reasonable prices.
Haven't been in years but happy to say RICE is still one of the best Thai restaurants in DC.

Amazing spot. Should have been busier than it was tonight, but we were happy to slip into a cozy, open window seat and watch the patrons of Le Dip wait around for their tables. The shrimp tempura plate was excellent. The brussel sprout salad intensely flavorful. The garden roll was absolutely delicious with mint leaves adding just the right freshness. The staff very attentive, courteous and helpful. Most definitely recommended. 5/5.
Delicious drunken noodles. Friendly people, cute environment.
Good food drinks were decent lovely staff
Great service and the food was awesome. Staff was very attentive and made us feel welcomed.
Not the cookie cutter Thai, good food
Amazing Thai food with quick service.
Okay.
Thai food that feels clean. They do it right here. Fun drinks too!

Rice serves up some classic Thai favorites in an urban chic space that emphasizes simplicity and warmth. Located in the 14th St corridor, Rice maintains the trendy, chic neighborhood vibe with its earth-toned interior and sleek, full-service bar. It can get pretty busy, so I’d recommend coming on the early-side to ensure you’re not sitting too close to any other loud patrons. The food is very good and they offer a nice array of options to pick from. They frequently have specials like a curry sampler. I’d recommend getting the Papaya salad with shrimp, Green curry with beef, and the Seafood basil. The presentation of food is tastefully done – simple and clean. The portion sizes are pretty good considering the prices. I strongly encourage you to look at the seasonal menu, so you can try some special foods. This is a great date night spot and wouldn’t be ideal for small children. There’s an outside patio with seating available for those nice weather days. They also have a small market at the entrance with lots of Thai cooking ware and trinkets.

Niiiiiice!!!! Food was flavorful & filling. Service was pleasant & professional. It sits along the busy life of 14th street, with plenty to see if you choose to dine outside. Highly recommend this place!
Me and my boyfriend ate here last year on our 2nd anniversary and today is our 3rd anniversary and we are headed back. Great food then and looking forward for another
Great food, great people, decent price. Loved the bento box.
Great location, friendly and efficient wait service. The green curry dish was delicious. Will be back again for certain.

Very nice asian restaurant. I had the Red Curry Chicken, it was very nice. It also liked the atmosphere, very modern but still classy.  I was there at around 6:30 pm and the place was almost empty. It is not expensive and really good, so I don't understand why.
(Translated by Google) it's delicious.  (Original) 맛있어요.
Nice place with good food. Will go back. Asian cuisine.

This is my go-to Asian takeout place. Curries and stir fry options are all solid. Drunken noodles also good. Service is fast and friendly. I am usually bag in hand and out the door 15 minutes after I've called to place the order. Recommended!
Awesome food and great patio
Quick service, Good portions easy in~out meal

I enjoyed my dinner here, the interior is cosy and the food very good. I had spring rolls and red curry and enjoyed both of my dishes. The one minus point was the temperature in the restaurant; I went on a hot day (about 85 degrees) and it was uncomfortably warm and stuffy in the restaurant.

I loved this neighborhood gem. Today was my first, but certainly not my last, time eating at Rice. The ambiance is warm and inviting, and the food is delicious. The drinks were also quite tasty - my lunch companion highly recommends the White Gummy Bear, which does in fact come with gummy bears at the bottom of the glass. My Dark and Stormy was strong, but not so much as to make it uncomfortable for me to be back in the office. Of particular note is the generous happy hour policy, which runs from open to 7pm on weekdays. I'm struggling to think of another restaurant which operates similarly.  Loved Rice and will definitely be back again!
Blech. Fake Hipster Thai. Avoid like the plague if you are familiar with authentic Thai cuisine. Go 4 blocks south on 14th Street to Baan Thai for true Thai food.
Wonderful!

Very helpful and friendly wait staff. They have a gluten free menu. Food was delivered fast and it was delicious. I ordered red chicken curry with vegetables and it came with a side of sticky rice. I  would definitely go back and recommend them. It was not busy so felt compelled to write this honest review. It's a nice restaurant.
Pad See Ew is my favorite here.

Really good happy hour, especially for the area. Portions are small for an American Thai restaurant, though probably in line with what you should actually be eating in one meal. Curries are rich and flavorful, the rice is to die for. I don't know what they do to make it sticky but not mushy (and it's not actual sticky rice) but it's amazing. Overall just a great spot.

Has an amazing ambiance, and the food tasted good, but I was served a microwaved, reheated meal! I got one of their special curries which had great flavor, a minute or two after ordering, my food came out. The meat looked like it was microwaved and some of the meat was cold. I’m not one to return food unless it’s really awful, but I was hungry and the flavors were good, not a big deal - Just disappointed.  There’s definitely better priced Thai food options on 14th.
Amazing food, great time.
It's one of those place where you have nothing bad to say but also nothing really caught my attention. Was it an experience to remember? No. Will I go again? Probably no.
It was fun and different for my birthday!
Best Thai food around, wonderful to-go and delivery options, amazing sticky rice desert.  Highly highly recommend.

Extremely over-priced. Foods are mediocre at best. If someone wants me to come back to this place he has to pay for me to do that.  I am a tourist and was looking for a nice thai restaurant in DC. Our quick search appears that this restaurant is a good choice. So we went there. As we entered we were pleased that this place was already packed with customers. Good sign. However one negative sign that I overlooked, in retrospect, was that asian:non asian customer ratio was too low. I consider high ratio is a good indicator of the quality/authenticity of asian restaurants.  I started with a tom yum soup and for the main entree I had their specialty three course thai curry meal. The tom yum soup that I had....my god...was the worst I have had so far. It was so watery and sour that I felt it was a ‘tom yum soup’ flavored vinegar. Besides liquid portion of soup, you will get a couple pieces of half mushrooms and tomatoes, and three shrimps in a small bowl. And they expect you to pay $8 + tips + 10% tax.  The three curry thing that I ordered was mediocre at best. It was initially fun to try three different types of curry. But first, in each bowl of curry, meat was not shredded or cut. It was a chunk of meat. If you plan to serve a chunk of meat, they where the heck is a knife? In asia we don’t use knife because meats are served precut so that they are already a perfect bite size. Without a knife it was extremely inconvenient to eat those meats. Also amount of rice : amount of curry ratio was low. This was $20 + tips + 10% tax.  So.. we ended up spending at least $25/person at there (I spent 31) for sub par food. You don’t even imagine how much I laughed when I found someone on google map review commented his experience “a party in the mouth”.
Great food and ambiance.
Loved it when they opened, still my favorite local restaurant!

Pretty standard Thai food, but still very good.  Not the most exciting place I've ever been, but it's a good place to go if you're looking for classic, yummy Thai food.  They're also very accommodating for allergies (they have a separate menu with all of the allergens labeled) and the staff is very friendly and will advise you and take allergies into account when making recommendations!
Creative Thai food. Brussels sprouts are amazing! Bangkok punch is sweet and strong.
Overpriced and under-spiced.

Super unassuming, especially with its higher profile restaurant neighbors, but great selection of Thai food. Recommend the drunken noodles with chicken, which had lots of chilies in it, making it spicy and balanced with the fresh basil.
The service here is always heavenly, never catch a bad attitude. Always super friendly and positive servers.
A very good version of a standard Thai place.
Rice is one of my favorite restaurants in DC. The food is consistently amazing and the rice (!) is incredible.

OMG it was like a party in my mouth!  We started with shrimp Tom Yum soup which was perfect, followed by red curry vegetables with shrimp and a wonderful sticky rice plus an order of pumpkin empanadas with delicious dipping sauce.  Kyle, the talented house mixologist created an innovative and fun sake gin martini.  Trendy atmosphere, attentive service, VERY reasonable pricing, flavorable and authentic cuisine with twists you'll love.  Highly recommended.   Went here instead of Baan or Teak wood and very happy with our decision.
Consistently delicious. Pad Thai with the fried egg on top is a safe bet. Recommend the red curry as well. Their appetizers are all a good start to a great entree.
This place was spot on. We randomly stopped by to have something to eat, and the Pad Thai ended up being absolutely delicious! So tasty!
Fantastic food
Love this place. Great food and staff. Outdoor seating and waiting is never a problem. Also great happy hour.
This a nice little gem on 14th Street. Highly recommended!
Average/mediocre food
A nice place for dinner.  Excellent food.  Pumpkin empanadas are great.  I love the saffron gin and tonics
Great Thai spot, the best on 14th St, serves the classics and a couple chef specialties.
Fine for small groups, but they are surprisingly unwilling to host larger parties.
Delicious food! Snapper bursting with flavor, Pad See Ew with chicken was delicious. Thai Iced Coffee and Iced Tea were both notably good.

Easily the best Thai food I've had in the city. The green and Panang curries are complex, yet true to what one has come to expect.  When you read "minimalist," don't worry that this is one of those restaurants that serve lozenge-sized food. True, the rice is pressed and shaped and you won't get as much of it as in a traditional Asian carry-out, but the rice is dense and perfect. You will not leave hungry.  Lighting and decor are very nice and understated, although you may need your cell phone flashlight to read the tiny menu type.
Their flavored rice is good
Beautiful, elegant Thai food.  They really like adding green tea in many dishes.  This is by far the best Thai I have had in DC.  The sticky rice with mango is phenomenal!

Warm, spicey, fresh -- just what I wanted when I slipped in for a quick dinner during a recent business trip.  The server recommended the green curry with chicken, with spicey level cranked up just a bit, vegetables (cabbage, carrots, red peppers) and sticky rice.  I used literally every grain of rice to soak up the sauce before relinquishing my plate to the bus person. The room was filling up as I was leaving but the wood decor was cozy and welcoming.  I'll be back soon.
The food was very good. The top 40 music less so

I never write reviews, but wanted to do this time as I liked the food so much!  So far I tried Panang, Green curry, padthai,  kaprow, and stick rice with mango.   They are all outstanding!  I also liked the attitude of people working there.  It is an excellent Thai restaurant, and am Confident one will be happy that they went there.
I was expecting a lot more.  The drinks are decent and their happy hour is more than fair.  I just wouldn't eat here.  The food is pretty lackluster.

Strolling 14th and U for a place to eat dinner, we walked into many restaurants.  Some were so busy that they had "frozen" the seating list (ahem, Barcelona).  Others were so noisy that even an open table couldn't pull us in.  Rice had immediate seating and a fine ambiance--a bit loud, but you get used to it and to having to shout a little to make conversation.  The food--excellent.  I got pad thai with chicken, my fiancé got the spicy duck.  We both Mmmed repeatedly throughout the meal, and were hesitant to offer the other person a second taste of our own deliciousness.  The garnishing and portioning were also fine, and our waters were refilled a lot.  For two people and two dishes (no appetizers, no drinks, no desserts), we were in and out for under $20pp.  Not terrible, though still a little pricy.  I'd happily recommend the place, and would certainly go back if friends invited me... otherwise I'll be checking out other great Thai offerings in DC.
Salad and soft shell crab are my favourite! Nice service!
Amazing place, clean facility and impeccable service the food is delicious, rich in flavors, tasty and yet healthy. Rice is definitely one of my favorite places to dine in DC
Love it.

Asian Spaghetti with anchovy and bacon??? Shrimp Spaghetti $15 @ Rice Restaurant, 14th st DC. (5/5 NOMs) I just had to to order this weird mix! It has bacon and anchovy in it. How often do you see something like that? Great dish and a sure thing to try at least ones. I couldn't taste the anchovy too much, but still enjoyed this very much. -

Omg YUMMY Thai food.  I love their menu pages - they are divided by styles of food, from classic to healthy to more contemporary / creative dishes.  The sticky rice could be a dessert in itself.  Awesome drunken noodles and excellent appetizers.

For N times I have been to this place, I have had the drunken noodles N-1 times.  And today I had the Penang Curry Chicken with Rice (spicy) and I was floored by the taste/quality/quantity of the entree! I only wish the quantity of rice was a little more than what I got. (But less rice is compensated with a lot of blissfully tasty curry!)  PS: I get stuff at this place to go, even then I am extremely pleased with the service and atmosphere (being offered a glass of water while waiting to pick up my awesome penang curry feels too good!)
